.\" shlib - A shell library of reusable functions
.TH SHLIB_SYS 3 "February 2026" "shlib 0.3.6" "Shell Library"
.SH NAME
shlib_sys \- System functions from the shlib library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B source
.I /path/to/shlib.sh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shlib_sys
provides functions for system interaction.
Requires Bash version 3 or higher.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Validation
.TP
.BI shlib::command_exists " command"
Check if
.I command
exists in PATH. Returns 0 if found, 1 otherwise.
.SH EXAMPLES
Check if a command exists:
.PP
.RS
.nf
#!/usr/bin/env bash
source /path/to/shlib/shlib.sh

# Check if a command exists
shlib::command_exists "commandname"
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I examples/sys.sh
Example script demonstrating system functions.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B shlib::command_exists
Returns 0 if command exists, 1 otherwise.
